plt.dataset

Class TrainableDataSet

  • java.lang.Object
    • plt.dataset.TrainableDataSet
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    PreprocessedDataSet

    public abstract class TrainableDataSet
extends java.lang.Object
    A TrainableDataset is a desired input for a preference learning algorithm. The difference between a DataSet and a TrainableDataset, is that the first must be considered an input as it is imported from a stream or a database, the second instead is wrapper of the first that can be used as inputs for the preference learning algorithm of this toolbox. PreprocessedDataSet for example is a TrainableDataset created by a DataSet and a list of preprocessing operation to apply to it. An important difference is that the features of a DataSet are String of a TrainableDataset are Double.
    Author:
    Vincent Farrugia, Luca Querella
